<span style="font-weight: 400;">Swine Flu spread all around the globe like an epidemic in 2009-2010. It is the name of the influenza type A virus that affects swine (pigs). However, during this epidemic, it spread as a combination of swine and bird flu along with a mixture of human genes. In this case, it came to be known as H1N1. Today, it is included in the flu vaccine.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) estimated that H1N1 affected nearly 61 million people in the USA and caused 12,469 deaths. All along the globe, 575,400 people died due to swine flu.</span>

