<b>Causes</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the myths about swine flu is that it can spread through eating pork. This is obviously not true. Influenza viruses affects your cells that line the nose, throat and lungs. The virus enters your body when you inhale contaminated droplets or take in live virus from a contaminated surface through your eyes, nose or mouth.</span>

